Dialogs.Dialog: Manaka
Say, do men...
Hmm？
...No, it's nothing.
Tell me, I'm curious.
It's just... It seemed like you didn't care...
...Like I didn't？
Geez. Don't look like you are having fun.
Forget it？ Okay？
(Instead, I'm even more curious！)
Hey... You were telling me about something, but you backed down.
Manaka
I asked you to forget it.
Of course I'll be worried if you tell me something like that.
Hmm... You know？
Yes, what is it！
...It's nothing.
Why？
Because when you are interested in something... your eyes are shining.
...Are they？ Look closer.
It's too late. I'm not going to speak about it, okay？
(That's a good defense...)
Will you tell me about what you don't wanted to talk last time ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
...You still remember it.
I'm worried！
Geez... It's not about me.
Ah, is that so？
Yes... You know？ A man, after getting out of the bath...
Is walking around the house with one piece of underwear a good thing？
Huh？
My friend was worried that her father didn't stop doing it, after telling him to.
I've never seen mine at home do that, so I couldn't give good advice.
Hey, do you know a good way？
(Hmm, I wonder how...)
Manaka
Do you remember about my friend who was worried about her father？ I think she gave up.
...Ah, the underwear dad？ Why？
It's fast to defend him. It seems that when her dad goes out of the bath, he should stay in his room.
Haha, that might be good.
...Hey, you do that too？ Being in your underwear after taking a bath...
Who knows... Maybe... Well, I live alone, so I don't need to be careful... Right？
T-that's right.
...Well then, I have to get used to it.
Huh？
No, nothing！
(How are you going to do that？)
Manaka
I wonder where every woman learns to do makeup.
Hmmー, I can't really imagine...
Mama seems to have gone to a beauty school and taught in an extracurricular class.
Emm, that doesn't seem to be the case at our school.
Is that so...？ I'll ask someone next time.
Do you want to put on makeup ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
I wonder if I should know a little. I want you to think I'm always cute...
You're still cute without it, okay？
...I won't be happy if you say it so lightly.
...Geez.
(Because it's true！)
Manaka
There are some girls in class who are very good at doing makeup.
One girl said that my face would look good with flashy makeup.
You with flashy makeup... Hmm, do you think it'll go well ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Don't you want to see it？
I want to see it, but do you think it's okay？
Hmm... Shall I try？ I'm kidding.
What if I say no？
Huh！ If you say no... It's no...
But, you want to see it？ Hey, tell me if you want to see, please？
(I want to give you courage...)
What happened to your plans to learn how to apply flashy make up Manaka？ You know, from the chat we were having before.
Manaka
Well, it was amazing... That was the first time I tried something like that...
Did you really put on make up！ Did you take a photo？
There is one... But I won't show it to you.
Eh, why！？
I'm using it as a reference to practice at home.
I want to master it and transform myself, before you see it.
Ah... I see.
Yes. That's why, can you wait a little more？
Yes, I'll wait！
Hehe, geez.
(This is fun！)
Manaka
I'm sorry. Flashy makeup has been banned.
Eh, why！？
Papa saw me practicing... "It's not something high school students should do！" he said.
...That was something amazing.
Yes. The magazine you referred me to, was also banned.
What magazine？
A gorgeous girl's magazine called "Papillon".
The hairstyle called "Mega" was amazing, so I imitated it. I asked Mama to help me...
My hair looked like a chocolate cornet and with my flashy makeup. Hehe, I got it bad.
Therefore, I'll try after graduating. Can you wait until then？
(Ah, it's a pity！)
Manaka
Ouch...
What's wrong, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
No, I'm fine, it's nothing.
Is that so？
Yes.
It's hurts...
Ah, maybe it's your teeth？
Huh... Yes. But, I'm fine！
(I hope she's okay...)
Did you go to the dentist, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
...What do you mean？
Don't you try fooling me. Weren't you in pain the other day？
Did that happen？
...Huh？
Geez, don't make things up. That story is new to me.
Hehe！
(She's telling me that... Are you afraid of dentists, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？)
Manaka
Hey. Have you been to the dentist recently？
Dentist？ Why？
I used to go there when I was little... So I was wondering how is it like now.
What if your teeth hurt in the meantime？
I don't think so...
You seem to brush your teeth daily and properly, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
I... I still can't forget that sound.
Huh？ What sound？
Like something was sharpening my teeth...
...No, it's okay, just forget it.
(I think your teeth are hurting you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
Are your teeth okay？
Manaka
Ah... I didn't want to make you worry, I'm sorry.
You were in pain.
Yes. I thought it was not good... So, I went to the dentist.
I see, I'm glad！ How was it？
A scratch on the gums was the cause of the pain, not the caries.
A scratch on your gums？ Why？
...You promise you won't laugh？
Of course！
I was brushing my teeth, right？ My hands slipped... I had too much momentum...
Ah, so that was it！ That happens a lot！
Haha... Ha！
I told you not to laugh. Geez, forget it！
(Oh, crap！)
Manaka
Say, do you know about any school to take special courses？
Special courses？ Do you want to learn something new？
No. It's not me, it's for Mama.
A lesson that only mothers can enjoy...
I don't think that would be good.
What do you mean？
I'd like something a little unusual that nobody does.
I see... If I think about something, I'll let you know.
Thank you. I'll leave it to you！
(A rare lesson...)
Manaka
You know？ I found some lessons Mama can take.
That's great. What kind of lessons？
Yoga, deco art and some walking.
Huh, that's surprisingly normal... no？
Yes. There were some strange things, but I didn't liked them as much.
I see. Was there something you wanted to try, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
There is！ A detective course.
Detective！？
But that seems like a school course rather than a lesson, so it seems impossible.
A little disappointing, if I must say.
(Detective... Does she like Holmes？)
Manaka
Mama started attending a yoga class.
Ah, she ended up doing yoga.
I wonder if she would teach me the poses. Doesn't it sound fun？
Why don't you try it then, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Hmm... I don't think I need to right now.
I would spend less time with you, and I don't like it.
Well, you have a point.
Right？ I'm kidding. But, wouldn't be nice if there were lessons two people could do, don't you think？
Certainly. Would you like to try？
Yes！ It will be fun▼
(I wonder what I should do.)
Manaka
I investigated some lessons two people can do together...
Oh. How did it go？
Golf, ballroom dance... and, pottery？
I see... I feel those activities are for adults, somehow.
Yes, they are a little different.
That's right. I mean, we play tennis already！
Ah... Hehe！ Yes, isn't that right？
Then... Want to learn how to become an adult？
Yes, let's do it.
It's a promise, okay？
Manaka
What's wrong with your hand？ Did you hurt it, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes... I cut my nails a bit too much.
Does it hurt？
I think so...？ Yes, quite.
I don't think it will affect me playing tennis or piano.
(Hopefully it's not a big deal.)
Are your nails okay ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Ah... Yes...
Can you let me see？
Hehe, do you want to confirm？ Here.
Okay, those are some really beautiful nails. Success！
Thank you▼
Huh？ What's wrong？
Ah, no！ Nothing！
(Did I do something bad？)
Manaka
I was speaking with my friends about nails and they told me "Why don't you do your own？"
Do your nails？ Like a manicure？
Yes, that's right. Like wearing glittery stickers, something like that.
I see. Don't you think that'll be nice？
Do you think so？ I want to try, but...
But？
There are club activities, and piano lessons, and...
Your parents will get angry.
Yes, so it's impossible.
(What's wrong with doing your nails？)
By the way, did you stop doing your nails, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Yes, I did. I can't make them shine, so I think it's just better to clean them.
Okay. Then, can I see the one you cleaned？
Here, this one please.
Yes, it's beautiful！ It's a full victory for you now！
Thank you.
(With nails this beautiful, you don't need stickers ▲高嶺＊＊▲！)
Manaka
...Hehe！
What's wrong？
Say, do you remember my rival？
Is it something related to your challenge games ▲高嶺＊＊▲...？
Yes. With that girl, I had an interesting game of making funny faces last time.
Funny faces？ Not stares？
Just staring at each other makes you laugh, right？ You can make a lot of funny faces.
And how much you can make the other person laugh...
Hehe... What should I do？ Hehehe！
(What was your face like？)
How is you funny face challenge going？
Manaka
She's getting better and better. I want to fight back...
Counterattack？ With an even funnier face？
Yes. But I have no idea what to do.
Let me think... Isn't the best strategy to imitate her？
Imitate her ways...
So it's no good？ Tell me what you want to do.
...It's no use, because her attitude isn't something that can be taught, but stolen.
Maybe looking at the mirror in the bath... Maybe it'll be useful.
(This can't be learnt in textbooks...)
Is your funny faces practice going well, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
I can do it better than before, I think？
But she's a few steps ahead, so I'm likely not going to win this time.
It's amazing enough you can do that much ▲高嶺＊＊▲...
Yes. Want to see？
I want to see！
I won't do it. If you become absorbed in it, I'll be in trouble.
"But Manaka belongs to me". I'm kidding.
(Eh, how did you...！？)
By the way, do you keep playing funny faces？
Manaka
No. It seems she got bored.
I see. I'm still interested in seeing your funny faces, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Hehe, you still don't have enough？
Yeah, it's a shame.
...I think so too.
You too, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes. I'm sure there are still so many. I want you to see a lot of my expressions.
I wish that too. I wonder when will you give up--
It might take a lifetime, you know？
Really！？
Sure！
Manaka
Huh？ What's wrong？
...Papa scolded me.
What？ Why？
I arrived a little late home. Mama protected me.
How much time？
About 5 minutes...
Eh, I think that much is okay.
I was the one who was late.
Hmmー, being a father is hard.
But he's kind. It's not that serious, so don't worry, okay？
Manaka
Living alone must be definitely tough...
Well, I find it a little comfortable. Why do you ask？
That is...
No way, do you want to live alone？
I was just thinking it a little.
Haha, you don't need to do that, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Maybe, but sometimes I want to stretch my wings.
Don't tell me you were scolded by your father, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
...Just a little.
Before was because you arrived a little late, what happened this time？
He found I was secretly watching a variety show.
(Just that！？)
Hey, did your father scold you again？
Manaka
A little more these days... But, thank you for worrying.
I'm was curious.
It's not a big deal.
But I don't think that's okay, I'm worried.
It's just... It was tough before, but these days I feel it's a little different.
How is it different？
I would say that recently he's been a little more unreasonable. I don't like that he's not making any sense most of the time.
I don't know. Seems like Papa is looking for any excuse to scold me...
This never happened in the past, right？
Yes...
(That's weird...)
Manaka
I understand now why Papa has been scolding me so unreasonably.
Oh, tell me！
Well, Mama thought it was weird and asked him.
She said "I think you've been tough on Manaka lately. Is something the matter？"
A straight, strong Mom. And then？
It was because of you.
You？ ...As in, me？
Yes. When I get home late after a date, make long phone calls, or send mails in the living room, he gets angry.
Haha...
Hehe, it was refreshing. Thinking back, Papa seemed a little cute.
(I don't find that refreshing...)
Manaka
What would you do if the wind was too strong to sleep？
Did that happen to you？
Yes. So I wish to take measures from now on.
But that doesn't stop you from falling asleep, right ▲高嶺＊＊▲...
Ah！ What do you mean？
Haha.
Geez. I couldn't sleep that day, and I was up until midnight.
(She certainly seems to be slow to sleep.)
By the way, with the chat we had before... How's your problem with the wind？
Manaka
Emm... The bucket on the balcony on the second floor is now gone.
Huh！ Did it fly away！？
Yes, but I'm glad I found it in the garden...
Something similar happened before, so it seems Mama was careful after that.
Something similar？
Yes. On windy days, she used to hang the pillows on the roof, and they flung over to our neighbors' houses.
And if it happened twice, then it'll happen thrice... And, I think it'll happen each time...
Yeah. Mama has a forgetful personality.
(So your Mom is unexpectedly forgetful, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？)
Manaka
I told you about my problems with the wind before, right？
Yes. Did you think about something？
Yeah, I thought something, but when I tried it, it failed.
Failed？ What did you do？
I tried wearing earplugs.
Then, I was worried about the sound of my breathing while I tried to sleep...
Ah, I understand.
I ended up staying up late, but I couldn't update the record.
I did something so half- assed, now I have to finish it.
(You're so hard working, ▲高嶺＊＊▲！)
By the way, what happened to your measures against insomnia during strong winds？
Manaka
Hehe, you say it so cool.
It's weird, you know？ It seems like I'm used to it now... I've been able to sleep normally, recently.
Oh, I'm glad then.
Hmm...
Huh？ Isn't that good？
It's because... I feel like I'm becoming less sensitive...
Don't worry about it. You see, even if you were like that――.
Ah！
You're trying to say I'm originally sober and insensitive, don't you？
(But you're nothing like that...)
Did something good happen to you today, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Do you want to know？
Sure, what happened？
You know, I been feeling a lot of love blooming within my friends.
Feeling of love？ How so？
They thought I was feeling anxious, so they've been sending me a lot of emails.
When they told me that, it looked like a lot of fun...
You say that, but you have a huge grin on your face, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Geez, I'm not grinning. But yes, it's something to grin about...
(Maybe something good will come up.)
You were telling me about how your friends have been kind to you so, how is it been going？
Manaka
Well, you see...
That grin... Did something good happened？
They're not only sending me mails, but talking with me on the phone.
Well, that's something to grin about.
Right？ I feel like I'm receiving so much happiness.
Yes. I was the same.
Love is a wonderful thing, right？ I'm glad I'm in love with you.
By the way, do your friends still send you mails？
Manaka
No. It's still been fun, though.
Well, I wonder if they changed their minds.
Yes... Ah...
You know？ I do have a message from my friends to you.
For me？ Why？
It says "One day, I want to have a double date, so I'll ask for your support".
Ah, that's what they mean. Bring it on！
Wouldn't it be nice if we could become their matchmakers？
Haha, like cupid？
That's right, maybe we shouldn't do things without thinking. Hehe.
As we were saying last time... What happened with the double date？
Manaka
Hmm... I think he wants a little more time, maybe？
Ah, I see. Even though I wanted to help.
But, my friend was very pleased with your reply, you know？
He was jealous of you, my reliable boyfriend.
Did you fall in love with me all over again？
I didn't.
Did you burn for me？
I've already done it.
Haha.
Hehe！
Manaka
Hey, have you ever let your beard grow？
A beard？ Yeah, I let it grow it sometimes.
And what about the friends of your father？
Whenever he comes back after drinking, he's thrilled about his beard.
So, I want to know why a man's beard was so stiff.
I think it's to protect something, I guess？
What？
Pride... I guess.
Pride？ Hehe, what do you mean？ That's... Hehe！
(I didn't mean it like that...)
Manaka
What？ Why are you staring at me？
No. I was wondering how'd you look like if you had a beard.
Would you like to see me as a great man like those in history books？
Yes.
That kind of beard seems to be quite hard to grow, you know？
I suppose. But I really want to see it.
Well... I know, a photo！ Let's draw on it first！ That way we can see it, right？
...Hmm, maybe...
(Phew...)
Did you try drawing the mustache, like we said？
Manaka
Yes. I asked a friend who is good at it, and we made various versions.
As expected of you... It's a nice touch you added ▲高嶺＊＊▲...
Well, in conclusion...
In conclusion？
I want to see the real one▼
That's what you expect to see？
Yes▼ Manaka would like to see you with one, okay？
I'm kidding... Teehee♪
(I-I see...)
Manaka
Hey, can you take a look at this？
Is this... a moustache？
Imagining it, I really want to see you with one.
...Here！？
Yes, it looks good on you. Can you stay like that today？
Huh！
A joke！
Can I take a picture？ I'll make it my treasure until I can see the real one▼
(A treasure...)
Manaka
Ah... It's mine！
I'm sorry. Recently, it seems my battery is running low too fast.
I see.
It's your fault.
Eh... mine？
Until I started dating you, I didn't use my cell phone so much...
...It's your fault, okay？
(It isn't because of me！)
By the way, how's your battery been doing now？
Manaka
Well... I was told I should buy a new battery, so I asked Papa but, you know what he did？
He just turned his mouth sideways, and was silent.
Huh？
I didn't even mention I was using it with you, you know？ He just ignored me.
Mama was frightened, even though she's usually calm.
And just like that, it's on hold for now.
But I won't run out of battery, so don't hesitate to call, okay？
(Her father's intuition is frightening...！)
It's about our last conversation about your battery. Did you convince your father？
Manaka
I didn't manage to convince Papa.
Huh, why？
You see...
If I use it properly, I think the battery will last longer.
I see... Then, should we look how to make a battery last longer？
...Yes！ Thank you.
Manaka
I got a new cell phone battery.
Great！ How did you manage to get it？
Papa mentioned there was a service that replaces used batteries for free.
Did he now... How did you really learn about it？
Well, I was sneaking around. Mama laughed at me when she realized I was disobeying.
...Your father is actually a kind guy.
Papa is always kind... Kind and scary.
I-I see... Well, I'm glad it worked out in the end！
Thank you. I have to use it carefully from now on.
Huh？ Are you wearing something different today ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Like what？
Your perfume or something it's different from usual.
...Ah. Is it because I changed my conditioner？
Ah, I see. Yes, it's nice.
...Hehe.
Hmm？
I'm glad you notice this little changes.
Especially you... My face might look weird, what should I do...
(This makes you so happy, huh.)
Your lipstick color is different！
Manaka
Huh！？ Uh, yes. I just bought a new one the other day.
I'm surprised you noticed it.
Of course！ I don't miss anything that changes about you！
Ah... I just remembered what I was happy about...
When I'm with you, I always feel like this.
Manaka
Huh？ What's wrong？ Why are you looking at me like that...
Is there anything special today？
Huh？
Umm, you know？ How should I say it...
I'm most happy when you notice the things I change about myself...
Right now, it feels like you're looking for mistakes, or...
Ah... I see. Sorry.
No, I'm glad you care. Thank you.
(I have to notice it naturally... Okay！)
Ah, your scent is back, isn't it？
Manaka
Yes. I used my conditioner again.
I see... Huh, was there something wrong with the new one？
Isn't it difficult to deal with girls？
Well... I don't think that's... true？
Hey, if you notice things you don't like, can you tell me？
I'm sure there are many things, so I'll solve――.
We will grow together！ Right？
Well said▼ I'm kidding.
Manaka
Hey, I have been wondering why I have to study.
Eh！？ Why so suddenly？
You see... a kid from my neighborhood asked me.
If I answered that it is because I was told that it would be really useful in the future...
Come to think of it, I just love studying... I couldn't say anything.
I see...
I wonder what should I answer if asked the same again. Hmmー...
(Why do we study...？)
Manaka
We spoke about why we should study, last time... I asked Mama about it too.
Yes. What did she say？
To expand our knowledge and to connect with other people.
But that's just Mama's reason, so I want to find out why I want to study.
...That's deep.
Yes. That's an opinion from an adult, right？ I feel we have different reasons.
I can't concentrate in class because I've been thinking about all this now.
I want to find the answer quickly...
(If you lower your grades, you'll be in trouble.)
Manaka
I asked Papa why we should study. He answered: So we don't regret it in the future.
So we don't regret it？
When you try to go back to school, after you become an adult, you can't do it without courage and action.
Therefore, if you don't want to do it when you have to, you'll have to do it as an adult. That's the smart way.
I see.
I felt some stress because there was some regret in Papa's voice.
Does he regret something？
It seems he wasn't good enough. If he had time, he would had liked to continue studying.
After the clinic time is over, you may be late to study outside of your field？
(If you don't study, you'll regret it... I get it, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.)
We spoke last time about why we should study. Have you seen the kid who asked you again？
Manaka
No. But next time they ask, do you know what I'll answer？
I'll say "I don't know if everything will be useful as an adult".
...I'd say yes.
But, isn't it bad to lie？
Well, that's also true.
But I don't know when it'll be needed, so we need to be prepared.
I see... Yes, that's true.
Phew... Finally, I feel refreshed.
Want to take a break？
Yes, I think I can finally enjoy studying after this.
Yeah！
Manaka
A friend in class was playing a game and I had a look.
Eh, that's unusual.
There's one thing I've been curious about it...
About what？
The male protagonist called himself "Ore-sama"... What do you think a girl should call herself？
Why are you worried about that？
Don't you think that's strange？ If you don't immerse yourself in the story, you can't empathize with her, right？
...Well, you might be right.
So I was thinking about it. Me-sama, sounds funny... So Manaka-sama sounds okay？
(I think your idea sounds really cute, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...)
Manaka
We were talking about the girl version for "Ore-sama" last time, right？
Did you think about something good？
A friend told me I could do it like "Myself".
Does it sound closer to "Ore-sama"？
...Maybe？
Doesn't it feel different？
My aunt and grandmother use it normally...
Mama says so in public places.
Hmm...
(Depends who and where you use it, I guess.)
Manaka
Last time we were speaking about "Ore-sama" and "Myself", didn't we？
Yes.
I think "M'self" is even closer.
Oh, that sounds about right！
I was curious, so I looked into it and found that there are many ways to do that.
For example？
For example, huh. Let's see...
Manaka Takane here, I'm from the tennis club！
Uh... Can you forget about it？ No？ I won't do it anymore, okay？
(I want to hear it again.)
Hey, last time we were talking about first-person pronouns, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Manaka
And, what's wrong？
Is it okay to make a request？
...You sure？
Sure！
...Then, just a little...
Yay！ Then say it a little boyish.
I am Takane Manaka...
It's a little different from what I thought.
...I'm Takane Manaka.
Yes. Next... a little more boyish.
...I'm Takane Makana... yo？
Hey, isn't it good like this？ Let's end this.
(Thank you！)
Manaka
Huh？ What's wrong？
...I was told it would be hard to have a popular boyfriend.
Me？ Who told you that？
Everyone in the tennis club.
...Am I that popular？
It's just that... everyone is saying it, you know？
And because you're so nice, how can't you be popular, right？
Geez... Geez...
(Should I be pleased, or... Hmm...)
Hey, last time we were speaking about how I was popular.
Manaka
...Yes.
That's definitely a lie. It's because I'm with you, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
How can you be so sure？
There's nothing I could do about it...
...Geez.
I wish I could hide you somewhere.
Hah...
(Isn't it bad to be so jealous？)
Manaka
Emm... What's wrong？
I think it's such a nice thing... But, no one is looking now...
...Are you talking about my popularity？ Is there something different？
Yes. Apparently, you're popular when we're together...
I see, that was it. Yes, that's right！
Huh？ The misunderstanding was solved, so why do you look at me like that？
Because...
Geez... Geez...
(Are you sure that's all you're worried about？)
We were talking about popularity last time, did you do something after？
Manaka
What's wrong？
Sorry for that time. I took everyone's joke and took a strange attitude...
Haha, it's okay. Anyway, it's good, this is over without problems.
Yes. From now on, stay the way you are, okay？
As I am？
Please stay with me, only me▼
Of course！ Please stay only with me too, ▲高嶺＊＊▲▼
Of course！ I'm kidding.
Have you been making sweets recently？
Manaka
What's wrong？ Is there something you want to eat？
If you make it, then anything is fine ▲高嶺＊＊▲▼
Geez, you keep saying that. Anything is really okay？
